/// eo9:net-virtio — the virtio-net driver world (plan/09, plan/12 D50's sibling).
///
/// `net.virtio` is the link-layer sibling of `disk.virtio`: it imports the PCI
/// capability (`eo9:pci/pci`), drives a modern (virtio 1.0, `disable-legacy=on`)
/// virtio-net PCI function through configuration space, BAR registers, and DMA buffers,
/// and exports `eo9:net/l2` — network interfaces, MAC addresses, and whole Ethernet
/// frames — so anything that speaks the link layer (an l3-over-l2 IP stack, a DHCP
/// client, the `l2check` example) runs over real hardware by composition:
/// `net.virtio $ program`.
///
/// `eo9:text/text` is imported only for one diagnostic line on first use (the probed
/// MAC address and queue sizes); the driver works identically without a console.
///
/// There is no configure interface: the documented default behaviour is to claim the
/// first virtio-net function visible through the granted PCI capability on first use
/// (the option-C default-configuration rule, plan/09 Decision 14). Selecting a specific
/// device address is `pci.filtered`'s job, composed in front of the driver.
package eo9:net-virtio@0.1.0;

world virtio-net {
    import eo9:pci/pci@0.1.0;
    import eo9:text/text@0.1.0;

    export eo9:net/l2@0.1.0;
}
